    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the design thing, but it feels like you're being a bit dismissive of the actual data showing people staying on benefits longer. if we look at the last few years, it's pretty clear that as the programs got bigger, the number of people working decreased. isn't it more accurate to say that these policies are fundamentally undermining the workforce instead of just being a 'design issue'?",
