      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is undeniable that the data shows correlations between expanded benefits and shifts in labor participation, which is precisely why the debate is so heated. However, attributing the decline solely to the policies ignores the broader economic forces at play, such as automation and wage stagnation. A more accurate view is that the safety net acts as a *response* to structural labor market changes, not the sole cause of workforce contraction. To definitively say the policies are \"fundamentally undermining\" the workforce is to ignore the role of external economic pressures.",
